Russia to Raise Crop-Sowing Area by 3%, State Press Service Says

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-03-18T08:54:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/russia-to-raise-crop-sowing-area-by-3-state-press-service-says.html
Russiaâ€™s government press service
said the  Agriculture Ministry  forecast the total sowing area for
all crops this year will increase 3 percent from 2010 to 77.2
million hectares (190.7 million acres).  The sowing area for spring crops is expected to be 50.4
million hectares, 3.5 million hectares more than a year earlier,
the press service said yesterday in an e-mailed statement. On
March 10, the ministry said 30 million hectares would be devoted
to grain plantings in spring.  Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  is scheduled to discuss
preparations for spring sowing at a meeting today, the statement
shows.  To contact the reporter on this story:
